nbsp; be&nbsp; poor. At one point of time, they seem to be mutually exclusive.&nbsp;</p>\n\n<p>So, one can imagine, one can intellectualize both the virtues and vices of money, but cannot truly see both of them (their development especially) at the same time, because the conditions required are&nbsp;mutually exclusive.</p>\n\n<hr />\n<p>A Short But Complete Guide To Becoming Adult:</p>\n\n<p>If you are child(-ish) and somehow feel pressured/suggested by the world that you need to become an adult; We present to you an (uniside) interview, with an adult:</p>\n\n<p>Hello! Yes, I am an adult! Aren&#39;t you? Then what are you, you sure don&#39;t look like a child!(?)</p>\n\n<p>Anyway, Let me tell you we adults are completely different from children, well, a lot different if not completely. I mean, we defitely find something funny when someone delivers a joke, and it becomes even funnier if they slide in some sexual words, some insult etc, you know!</p>\n\n<p>But apart from that we are very different from children. Okay, let me just tell you about myself and then you can figure out what&#39;s different, since you are a child, right?</p>\n\n<p>For one thing, I don&#39;t have the innocence that children have.&nbsp;</p>\n\n<p>I don&#39;t just enjoy something, I plan to make it <em><strong>my own</strong></em>.&nbsp;</p>\n\n<p>I can tell a lie, or hide something, and not even giggle, or leak any suggestion. And even if someone is able to get a hint, I can strategize even better to become better at hiding.</p>\n\n<p>My games are different from children, I don&#39;t play with toys, or just enjoy some activity, someone&#39;s company, I happen to make plans, I happen to <em>strategize</em>&nbsp;whom should I play with, where do I get the maximum amount of pleasure, not only for now but also which can help me develop a relationship that will help me later. My games are based on playing with emotions, secretive actions. I don&#39;t just say what&#39;s on my mind, I frame it in a way that will give me advantage. Yes, I am very fond of advantage.</p>\n\n<p>You see, I can use anything to my advantage. I practice it and I become better at it.</p>\n\n<p>I can use not only <em>things</em> to my advantage, but also people. When I see someone, I don&#39;t just see a person, I see opportunity, and it&#39;s not something that <em>I</em> do, it&#39;s &quot;natural&quot;, it&#39;s automatic. I engage with a person not just to be, but to form a relationship, for various reasons you know, like a relationship that will help me &quot;grow&quot;, help my &quot;business&quot; grow.&nbsp;</p>\n\n<p>I don&#39;t just care about here and now, I care about future as well. You see, I am very fond of security. I want security, and this doesn&#39;t mean security from harmful animals only, but also from anything that could happen, also from that is unlike me, or a sitution not desirable to me.</p>\n\n<p>You look confused! Hah! You dumbass children!</p>\n\n<p>Anyway, here&#39;s a better word to describe it - Control. I want control. I want things to be my way, I want to control everything, I want control over animals, not only harmful but also weak ones, especially the weak ones. I want control nature.</p>\n\n<p>You see when I look at a tree, or something that&#39;s part of nature, I don&#39;t just look at the thing. I look at something that cane be controlled, transformed into something else which will provide me more of security and control.</p>\n\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n\n<hr />\n<p>About Free-Will</p>\n\n<p>Two angles to look at it.</p>\n\n<p>1. Everything is caused by something, so we can say that no effect is free from causes. When we make conscious choice, there are unconscious factors involved. Unconscious factors are based on a lot of events, including physical events within and outside body. Hence, apparently no will is completely free. But there is another way to look at it, which involves complexity. In a complex system, even though the current state is dependent on the past states, one cannot predict the future states. So, in a way, future state is &quot;free&quot; from the present state. And, a simple manifestation of this appears in case of fractals.</p>\n\n<p>2. From another angle, this question that whether free-will exists or not becomes futile. Here&#39;s how:</p>\n\n<p>If you combine Plato&#39;s Allegory of The Cave, with a movie named &quot;The Trueman Show&quot;, you can see that reality is always an illusion. Why always? Because at any layer, you don&#39;t expect that there&#39;s an outer layer, and yet you cannot prove it. So, you can <em>accept</em> that the illusion itself is reality, and the ultimate reality will be the layer beyond which you don&#39;t have mechanism to go. Which means that your reality is an illusion, and if the reality itself is an illusion, then free-will being an illusion could itself be an illusion. So, the question becomes futile in the shadow of another question, &quot;Is the reality an illusion?&quot;.</p>\n\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n\n<hr />\n<p>Santa Fe Courses MOOC:&nbsp;https://www.complexityexplorer.org/courses</p>\n\n<hr />\n<p>At the root of all problems lies our quest for pleasure. As a dark example, take slavery, there were two forms of slavery, those who used slaves for some work, and if they had little sense they understood that a slave needed to be given life-preserving resources in order to gain maximum ouput, which would be pretty much the same as now the way jobs work. The other was where slave owners took pleasure from the agony of slaves, they didn&#39;t care much about maximum output.</p>\n\n<p>We are seeing so much peace right now in the world, is it going to continue for a very long time (forget &#39;always&#39;)?&nbsp;</p>\n\n<p>What reason do we have to believe so, when it is clear that our drive for pleasure has not changed much, in fact the whole cultural lifestyle is making humans more slave to their desires. Every single item on market is up for making you more of a slave to desires.</p>\n\n<hr />\n<p>Inevitable forces of Capitalism....</p>\n\n<p><a href=\"https://youtu.be/2GFaN9-1iz0?t=1607\">https://youtu.be/2GFaN9-1iz0?t=1607</a></p>\n\n<p>How long would it take Capitalism to go into such areas? Will it ever go there on its own?</p>\n\n<p>Corporate&#39;s responsibility?:&nbsp;<a href=\"https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=_jed8B4L4-4\">https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=_jed8B4L4-4</a></p>\n\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n\n<hr />\n<p>I would like someone to put forth a counter-argument to this:-<br />\nApart from what is directly perceivable by humans, there&#39;s something more, called imagination.&nbsp;<br />\nNow imagination comes in two forms: one based on images, for example a unicorn, or mermaid, or dragon.&nbsp;<br />\nThe other form is purely a concept, for example &#39;nothing&#39;, &#39;infinite&#39;, &#39;eternal&#39;, &#39;immortal&#39;..&nbsp;<br />\nIf you observe carefully, you see that first form seems quite plausible, we perceive images, images get modified and we come up with, say, something like dragon.&nbsp;<br />\nBut, where does the second form of imagination come from? They have no correspondence to anything observed. And, yet it has been present in human cognition for like forever..&nbsp;<br />\nSo, it can be said that these concepts are built into the fabric of human cognition. So is God, you can say that it&#39;s imagination, but actually it&#39;s just built into fabric of human cognition.&nbsp;<br />\nBut yeah, personal God seems like imagination of first form, as evident by gods in various cultures.</p>\n\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n\n<hr />\n<p>When you deal with a lot, it becomes easy to forget the most simple and the most important things. (It happens a lot while coding)</p>\n\n<hr />\n<p>https://nlp.stanford.edu/~johnhew/rnns-hierarchy.html</p>\n\n<p>https://slatestarcodex.com/2014/07/30/meditations-on-moloch/</p>\n\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n\n<p>What do I think about Life?</p>\n\n<p>A lot! But the main&nbsp;thing is that &quot;truth&quot; about Life is not very pleasant. So, the only question relevant for me is how to conduct myself given the situations we&#39;ve got? Clearly, dependence on others is not something helpful. Clearly, rejection (that produces enmity) of others is not helpful. Clearly, others&#39; lifestyle is not helpful for me. Clearly, fear is not helpful.</p>\n\n<hr />\n<p>Jim Carrey says, &quot;(When you go into&nbsp; the character deep enough) If it is so easy to lose Jim Carrey, then who the hell is Jim Carrey&quot;</p>\n\n<p>You can realise this thing by other means as well. How easy it is to lose &#39;yourself&#39; under the influence of intoxicants. There are some aspects of you that persist through intoxicated state more than others. But, it&#39;s all, your whole being is transitory.</p>\n\n<hr />\n<p>For a long time I thought, what&#39;s the importance of telling dates like when some important figure was born, when he died and so on.</p>\n\n<p>But now I realise that it&#39;s not completely irrelevant, it can be&nbsp;interesting, even useful. And it becomes clear if you have some context of the world around those dates.</p>\n\n<p>But any/much context, when I studied dates in school it seemed toturous.&nbsp;</p>\n\n<p>But how would you give context to early year students? - There can be many techniques, one can be to make them think about their local history (family, locality, city etc), another can be simply remind them (make them wonder) how close or far off that date is. The idea is that somehow, you have to link the dates with whatever content students have in mind.</p>\n\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n\n<hr />\n<p>I have now seen this 2-3 times happen that when a person is mentioned by me or to me after a (very) long time, she appears in my dreams.</p>\n\n<hr />\n<p>https://aeon.co/</p>\n\n<p>Science of Life</p>\n\n<p>Evolution - Wallace&#39;s book, The Deniable Darwin, Darwin&#39;s Doubt</p>\n\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n\n<p>Science of Mind</p>\n\n<p>Study on Schizophraniacs</p>\n