i/</p>\n\n<p>Municipalism,&nbsp;<a href=\"http://fearlesscities.com/\">http://fearlesscities.com/</a></p>\n\n<p><a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Goldilocks_principle\">https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Goldilocks_principle</a></p>\n\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n\n<p>Reading material:</p>\n\n<p>https://link.springer.com/article/10.3758/s13423-015-0931-3</p>\n\n<p>https://link.springer.com/article/10.3758%2Fs13423-015-0890-8</p>\n\n<p>https://link.springer.com/search?facet-discipline=%22Education%22</p>\n\n<p>https://neurotree.org/beta/publications.php?pid=48818</p>\n\n<hr />\n<p>I am a sort of anti-developmentalist (actually I am no &quot;-ist&quot;, but this resonates with me) especially all the developments that have been done which are not life-affirming (One clear example of life-affirming&nbsp;would be medical developments which prevent us from external threats like viruses, life-affirming would be an arguable concept though!).</p>\n\n<p>If you see the current situation there are people trying (and supporting) to make extra-ordinary technological advancements, and some people criticize that. And what&#39;s interesting is that both of them focus on the same thing - life. Some say that all these technological advancements like AI/AGI, Extra-terrestrial Life&nbsp;etc are all necessary because we know that Earth is not going to be habitable forever, we need a Plan-B. So, basically they are thinking about continuing Life as we know it. Some say that these technologies are life-threatening. So, they are also thinking about Life as we know it.</p>\n\n<p>I guess the first type of people are more brave in exploring the possibilities probably because they&nbsp;are not content with the current situation of Life, or probably because they have more fear of Death deep down, I have a skepticism that they really care what is going to happen to the human species after let&#39;s say 1000 years in the future. The second type of people want to focus on what they&#39;ve got from nature already.&nbsp;</p>\n\n<p>And then there are third type of people who are ignorant of all these things going on!&nbsp;</p>\n\n<hr />\n<p>A learning from Software Development:</p>\n\n<p>Some people complain about usage of frameworks, and how they have been growing in number. They are more likely to encourage people to skip/forget the fundamentals and hence cause damage.</p>\n\n<p>The same principle can apply in life as well. With all the modern toys that keep people busy, they get overwhelmed with it, and things start owning them.</p>\n\n<p>Now, if you try to tell someone to discourage using the frameworks, they are clearly not gonna listen to you. And even if someone listens and believes you, they might not be able to follow this advice. So, the middleway for developers is: use fraeworks, but try to customize it often, that way you&#39;d be forced to learn the fundamentals of the frameworks.</p>\n\n<p>Similarly, the middleway for life is: do whatever you want to do or have to do. But try to practice minimalism often.&nbsp;</p>\n\n<hr />\n<p>I find a lot of similarities between seemingly unrelated events and concepts. An example, you see nowadays information flooding all around. People are exchanging so many motivational quotes and stories for success. But not everyone who reads them get inspired (at least to a significant degree). What&#39;s going on there? The person is getting the relevant motivation, information etc and still no impact?&nbsp;</p>\n\n<p>Now take the same structure of event and apply it to what happens when and if people are informed about virtues and ethics. Socrates (through the writings of Plato) said that a person will automatically do the right thing if he knows what&#39;s right.&nbsp;</p>\n\n<p>What I am seeing here is that even if a person has the information about what&#39;s &quot;right&quot; he might not do it.&nbsp;</p>\n\n<p>There&#39;s a different set of configuration required for each possibility, be it striving for success, striving for peace/contentment, striving for morality, striving for hedonistic/irresponsible pleasures, or whatever.&nbsp;</p>\n\n<p>And even if a person comes to see what is right and what is wrong, choosing to do the right thing takes an immense amount of energy, the lack of which will result in the person settling for the &quot;wrong&quot; anyway.&nbsp;</p>\n\n<p>What does it mean?&nbsp;</p>\n\n<p>Well, not much. Just the same old philosophy that there are two forces in nature good, and evil. And will continue!&nbsp;</p>\n\n<p>But I am interested in conversions between good and evil.&nbsp;</p>\n\n<hr />\n<p>My expectations from Technology, Science and &quot;Progress&quot;:</p>\n\n<p>We have seen tremendous progress in technology in recent years (not so much in science though). And we thought that technology will enlighten (Western enlightenment) people.&nbsp;</p>\n\n<hr />\n<p>I was trying to clear my thoughts regarding education, and I found that there&#39;s an important distinction that needs to be made between just&nbsp;<em>education</em>&nbsp;and education referred as in education-system. Seems silly right? But I think the problem is that the word&nbsp; &quot;education&quot; does not represent the same thing in both contexts. There&#39;s hardly ever any effort in terms of education. There&#39;s lot of effort in education-system&#39;s education. Education can not be done by any organized system, unless you everyone settles on some clear guidelines for life and stick to that. Education is tightly connected to life. Whatever direction the life goes in, education must go. Whatever priorities life takes, education must help. Education cannot be responsibility of one particular group or person. Everyone must take part in a person&#39;s education - parents, neighbors, friends, relatives, teachers etc. On the other hand, educaiton as referred in education-system is only meant for keeping the established system running, and it can be handled by some particular group e.g. teachers.</p>\n\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n\n<p>To people who talk about Truth, if I really seek truth, I can pick fault in almost all statements. But that would not be likeable to you. It&#39;s quite clear, that it&#39;s not about truth, it never has been.</p>\n\n<p><strong>On Development:</strong></p>\n\n<p>We have seen tremendous development in recent years of human history, so much so that we don&#39;t even have any idea where the technological development will take us in coming years. Personally, during my own life, things have changed so much from childhood to now.</p>\n\n<p>But when we say &#39;development&#39;, we are not being precise, and hence not being honest. The point is that we have seen tremendous development but only on one facet, on materialistic level.&nbsp;We now have more comfort, more gadgets, more <strong><em>toys</em></strong>&nbsp;in one form or another.&nbsp;</p>\n\n<p>The best outcome of this sort of development that I won&#39;t argue, is the increase in life-saving medical technology. (And I know the development of medical technology is linked with other technologies in some way, but that&#39;s beside the point).</p>\n\n<p>If you see on human leve, psychological level, spiritual level, there has been <strong><em>zero</em></strong>&nbsp;development (Note: I&#39;m not saying this on the basis of data). People still live their life driven by the same fundamental psychological forces, and people will always will (probably). But the&nbsp; question is which forces of psyche are&nbsp; prevalent, more potent overall in&nbsp; the human civilization. <em>Is it love, is it compassion, is it natural happiness, is&nbsp; it peace and pure energy?</em> I won&#39;t say ccoperation (because co-operation is secondary, even two enemies might cooperate sometimes). <em>Is it fear? Is it jealousy? Is it pride, feeling&nbsp;of superiority? Is it prejudice? Is it envy? Is it fear of loneliness? Is it demand for conformity&nbsp;and validations?</em></p>\n\n<p>One might give example of how we have been peaceful, we have had no war for over 50 years. I would like to invoke a thought experiment then:</p>\n\n<p><em>Suppose you find that a virus has entered in your body, and you fall sick. But after a few days of sickness, you get better. But by every possible mean you know that the virus is still there in the body. What would you say then, has it really gotten better? Is there a progress? Maybe the virus is on hiatus, it&#39;s mutating, and it will strike back.</em></p>\n\n<p>You see our whole life, and hence the whole journey of humanity in general is being driven by the same elements. There&#39;s no real development at all.</p>\n\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n\n<p><strong>On Pride:</strong></p>\n\n<p>This is a recurring theme, a pattern in society overall: Pride, and Feeling of Superiority. The feeling&nbsp;could be result of money, education, talent etc. People feel themselves superior to some of the others, and it seems that it is necessary&nbsp;for their stable existence. You could write/read books about pride, why it is necessary and so on. What I feel though&nbsp;is that&nbsp;those who feel superior, or proud are stupid in one dimension, even if a <em>genius</em> in other dimensions.&nbsp;</p>\n\n<p>If you analyse the cause and effect of all the events and in this world, you&#39;ll see that every effect has a cause. Combined with the fact that sometimes seemingly minor causes can result in&nbsp;major effects, the whole web/network of&nbsp;cause-effect becomes too complex to analyse. And again, if you analyse the&nbsp;events going on with you internally, you&#39;d find that there&#39;s a&nbsp;cause for each&nbsp;of your mental&nbsp;state, and at some point the&nbsp;cause is beyond your control (or even your attention).&nbsp;</p>\n\n<p>Overall, whether there&#39;s free-will or not, the fact is that your current state is a function&nbsp;of a lot of states and events beyond your own control (or even&nbsp;your attention). You can make yourself happy by assuming&nbsp; that <strong><em>you</em></strong> achieved something, or that&nbsp;<strong><em>you</em></strong> made a wrong decision in&nbsp;life&nbsp;and so on. But this&nbsp;happiness, this stability of your self, when&nbsp;comes at cost of obvious (observational) facts, and is reinforced again&nbsp;and again,&nbsp;the happiness not even remains the main driving factor&nbsp;any longer. Pride, Superiority complex, Looking down at others, Looking yourself as provider and others as consumers, and so on, all these things become a force in themselves.&nbsp;</p>\n\n<p>But the &quot;truth&quot; doesn&#39;t matter to many. So, even then when someone looks down at someone else and feels superior,&nbsp;why doesn&#39;t he/she think that at the same time there are people superior to them?&nbsp;Why doesn&#39;t that fact neautralize their&nbsp;feeling of superiority? &mdash; Ignorance, and because those forces that were developed by reinforcement have become stronger than their core psyche.</p>\n\n<p>If they can&#39;t find anyone superior, they should notice that despite their possession (of money, education or talent) they <em>require</em> something <em>desperately</em> &mdash;&nbsp;&nbsp;external validation, so called <em>&quot;respect&quot;,&nbsp;</em>and there are people who don&#39;t even&nbsp; require that. Why don&#39;t they consider that this requirement of theirs trumps what they&nbsp;possess.&nbsp;</p>\n\n<p>You can expand the same to groups/classes, and see that group feelings of superiority has similar stupidity.&nbsp;</p>\n\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n\n<hr />\n<p>A poem in progress:</p>\n\n<p>Philosophers Last Moments:</p>\n\n<p>[God appears and says] Fool, you spent your whole life in images [insert a word for abstraction, close to image], and ignoring the beauty of the world, the people, the trees, the oceans, the mountains, the maginficant achievements of people. [Philosopher] smiled and said, you too are an image, aren&#39;t you? Half of the world is running after you, for you, on the commands of you, and yet you never appeared among those people, those mountains and trees. Now I&#39;ve seen both you and the beauty created by you. No repentance!</p>\n\n<hr />\n<p>Do plants have life? Do mountains have life? Do stones have life?</p>\n\n<p>Absolutely not. It&#39;s silly to say that they have life. Right?</p>\n\n<p>OK. But with more and more science what we are discovering is that you, me also function almost in the same way as machines do. Only thing is that you, me have more complex machinary and more properties.&nbsp;</p>\n\n<p>To me, sometimes it seems that even humans do not have life. They are just some sort of processing.</p>\n\n<p>On other times, it seems that even plants have life. Maybe the life perceived outside in other entities depends on the amount of life that is within me. And I can imagine an extreme possibility, when I am so full of life that everything that I touch by perception also seems to have life.</p>\n\n<p>Maybe similarly the amount of intelligence within decides what intelligence (and in which entities) I perceive outside.</p>\n\n<hr />\n<p>I have long been confused about what is right and wrong. Logic fails in most of the scenarios when it comes to making decision about right and wrong.&nbsp;</p>\n\n<p>But now I have theory which can solve it for most of the scenarios. It depends on complexity. More complexity some action generates, more chances there are that it would be wrong. Take lying for example: Is it wrong to lie? Everyone would agree that some small lies which do not cause some harm are fine, are not wrong. Although this demands&nbsp;further analysis, what is harm, what degree of harm, and how much this small lie can contribute to bigger lies, or how much subtle effects can this lie has etc. This analysis demands a lot. Our minds has intrinsic capacity to identify what is complex and what is not. If our minds sees no (or very little)compexity related to some action, the action can be considered good.</p>\n\n<p>Let&#39;s test it on something that is very hard problem. What about something like Euthanasia? If it gets to a point where there&#39;s no complexity involved, it is not wrong to help someone die who is suffering. What does the complexity mean here? These are the examples: the person who is suffering wants to die, but is not completely sure. There are relatives which want him to not suffer, but are not sure about the action. In case of complexity, it would be considered wrong.&nbsp;</p>\n\n<hr />\n<p>https://www.pitt.edu/~jdnorton/teaching/HPS_0410/chapters/index.html</p>\n\n<p>There are few &#39;sometimes&#39; which are not very obvious:-</p>\n\n<ul>\n\t<li>Sometimes people help others in order to be help themselves</li>\n\t<li>Sometimes people would never have fallen in love, had they not heard the word love.</li>\n\t<li>Sometimes you don&#39;t really like the things you think you like</li>\n</ul>\n\n<p>https://jsxgraph.uni-bayreuth.de/wiki/index.php/Documentation Use this to create animations for Euclid&#39;s Elements.</p>\n\n<p><a href=\"https://www.fil.ion.ucl.ac.uk/~karl/\">https://www.fil.ion.ucl.ac.uk/~karl/</a></p>\n\n<p><a href=\"http://patrick.maher1.net/317/lectures/\">http://patrick.maher1.net/317/lectures/</a></p>\n\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n\n<p>Cooperation based Economy:&nbsp;<a href=\"https://web.archive.org/web/20131105113916/http://bnp.binghamton.edu/wp-content/uploads/2011/06/Ostrom-2010-Polycentric-Governance.pdf\">https://web.archive.org/web/20131105113916/http://bnp.binghamton.edu/wp-content/uploads/2011/06/Ostrom-2010-Polycentric-Governance.pdf</a></p>\n\n<hr />\n<p>&quot;By a small sample we may judge of the whole piece, Miguel de Cervantes &ldquo;Don Quixote.&rdquo; This supports my doubt that all this data-oriented thinking is gonna contribute to stereotyping.</p>\n\n<hr />\n<p>I need only two things capability to fill my stomach [with food] when I need, empty my mind when I want.&nbsp;</p>\n\n<hr />\n<p>Problem of banalization.&nbsp;</p>\n\n<hr />\n<p>I&#39;m really a stupid person. People want to become leaders, and here I am wanting to end the necessity for leadership.</p>\n\n<hr />\n<p>I&#39;m a slow learner, it took me really long time to figure out why all these gurus (from all realms) expound so much when there&#39;s very little to say in actuality, why everyone is trying so much to emphasize the theories that they believe in. It&#39;s not that they cannot grasp the counter-theory, or that they don&#39;t realize that what they know is not the whole truth, or that it&#39;s not even truth, or that nothing is truth. It&#39;s because for learning it takes attachment, to form the attachment they have to expound so much, link their ideas with as much aspects of life as possible. All of this for what? One thing is that they are also instruments of ideas, just like bodies of each organism are instruments of genes. The other thing could be that whatever truth they have found or believe in, they need support for that, and they would do everything in their capacity to gain support. And the basis of all this is attachment.</p>\n\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n\n<p>All those saints, is/was there any real significance to them?<br />\nWhat is the significance of any of your relation? with your parents, spouse etc?<br />\nYou can see it in terms of consequences, impact on you. You can also see it in terms of mechanism. You can ask the objective, metaphysical/ontological questions like does my love really exist for my spouse, or for my parents?<br />\nSo, if a saint serves some purpose for the people associated, then how can we deny his significance any less than significance of our other relations?<br />\nAnother question worth asking his why even need for this?<br />\nSo, the need for your parent&#39;s association is development, need for spouse&#39;s association is sustainance and propagation of life. In both cases, there&#39;s something lacking in you which these relations serve. In the same way, there must be something lacking in those people who associate themselves with saints.<br />\nYou can say that they also associate because of unknown (and stupid) fear, or because an impractical hope.<br />\nThere&#39;re two ways to look at this then:&nbsp;<br />\n&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;1. Yes, but you&#39;ll find that fear, and expectation also present in your other associations. You can then say that but their expectations and fear is irrational. That goes into a deeper question: what&#39;s even rational, why any fear is needed, why any life is needed, why some person has one sort of expectation, fear, passion, and another person some different version of it. Why do we lack anything at all? Why are there emotions at all? etc<br />\n&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;2. Even if that&#39;s true that their fears, expectations are irrational, the association serves some purpose. Which is all that matters to those people. You can say that they need to upgrade themselves. But, then the question is that can you downgrade yourself to their level? If not, then why expect them to upgrade? There are transformations happening obviously, but transformation is a process so complex that someone&#39;s suggestion is of very effect.</p>\n\n<p>Is it even possible to love everybody as claimed by/for those saints?<br />\nChoose the person you love the most. Imagine they get hurt, would you feel pain/sorrow? Why? There&#39;s no physical/mechanical association between you two. The other person can be poles apart, and you would still feel the pain? Why? Because, it&#39;s generated by your mind. Now, your mind must have some mechanism, some condition that must be satisfied to generate that sort of love. Imagine if those conditions are very limited, so limited that almost everyone satisifies them. Then your mind can generate love for almost everyone.</p>\n\n<hr />\n<p>Tricks of Carl Jung<br />\nhttps://www.youtube.com/embed/Ed3vPb9bmcw?start=1112&amp;end=1287</p>\n\n<p>Carl Jung on archetype<br />\nhttps://www.youtube.com/embed/Ed3vPb9bmcw