ost of the scenarios), it gradually started guiding the development of women&nbsp;<br />\nwithin the framework of that stereotype.&nbsp;<br />\nAnd, as you have seen in the past, none of the stereotypes is immune to change, at some point of time there will be demand to fix the stereotype. And you see,<br />\nthe more the stereotype has been exercised, the more impactful it has been, the harder it will be change, the bigger revolution it will demand, and more havoc it will cause.</p>\n\n<p>You might say that man has advanced so much in intellect that such mistakes will not happen. But remember, the world has always been intelligent enough as seen from the present time as point of reference i.e. our previous generations would have thought the same thing.&nbsp;<br />\nPlus, the world is not run by intellect as much as by feelings and emotions.<br />\n&nbsp;</p>\n\n<hr />\n<p class=\"mentions-texteditor__content\">I know what I really want now in my life. I want to develop methodoglogies which can automatically develop intutions.</p>\n\n<hr />\n<p class=\"mentions-texteditor__content\">Is understanding even the main thing in mind. It feels that belief is more fundamental thing. Look at this: I see videos of these philosophers, found their theory and idea. Now if I go read their books, the same thing that they told in a compressed manner will be linked through many pieces, and extensive explanations which when registered in mind gives me an illusion of understanding.</p>\n\n<p class=\"mentions-texteditor__content\">Here&#39;s what I observe in understanding: my find has already accepted some things, and then tries to make connection of new data, concepts by pivoting against those accepted facts.&nbsp;</p>\n\n<p class=\"mentions-texteditor__content\">But, during that process all I have done is formed multiple logical connections reaching the same thing. Is that what understanding is about? Forming logical pathways? Then, the main thing is not these pathways, but the terminal node which is understanding. And what&#39;s interesting is that you can have this terminal node ahead of the logical progression, or as a result of the logical progression. It&#39;s still the same thing.&nbsp;</p>\n\n<p class=\"mentions-texteditor__content\">And, in case when you do not have a (or, more) terminal node(s), you don&#39;t have anything. Not even understanding.</p>\n\n<hr />\n<p class=\"mentions-texteditor__content\">It&#39;s childish&nbsp;to dichotomize people.</p>\n\n<p class=\"mentions-texteditor__content\">Take for example, dichotomy of materialist and immaterialist. When Roger Pensrose was asked about this, he replied &quot;I used to call myself materialist, but I now I don&#39;t understand what is material&quot;</p>\n\n<hr />\n<p class=\"mentions-texteditor__content\">Picturisation of existential crisis:-</p>\n\n<p class=\"mentions-texteditor__content\">Imagine that in your house, there&#39;s a room to which you never really paid attention to. This is not a house that you built consciously, it&#39;s a house that you got, it just was there, and you found yourself living in that house. Sometime it just happened that you opened this neglected room, and as you go into this room and spend some time, something bizzare happens; you start questioning everything. So far you never worried about how you got into the house, you just lived there enjoying the parts of it, but now you start questioning where did the house come from, how did I get into this house, why am I living here, why is it (the house) even there, and so forth. You find yourself into bizzare situation. Fortunately you get pulled out of this room. You try to get back to your normal days, but you can&#39;t undo your experience with that room, and you still living the house.&nbsp;</p>\n\n<p class=\"mentions-texteditor__content\">Now, if this doesn&#39;t sound like your story in any regard, you are lucky that you never came across that room in your house, or that room has a heavy, strong lock on it. If you are lucky enough, you will get through your whole life without ever opening that room.&nbsp;</p>\n\n<hr />\n<p class=\"mentions-texteditor__content\">It&#39;s best to keep physical and spiritual separate. Mathematics is the best language for physical domain, silence is the best language for spiritual domain. Mathematical and scientific advancement is not only necessary, it&#39;s given, we can&#39;t stop it, we may try to enhance it. But expecting that mathematical and scientific advancement is going to solve everything. As long as &quot;you&quot; are there, you&#39;ll have same problems, degree might be different, form might be different, but on a fundamental level it will remain the same.</p>\n\n<hr />\n<p class=\"mentions-texteditor__content\">I don&#39;t know what this feeling is. It seems that it&#39;s stopping me from just &#39;being there&#39;, there&#39;s a disquiteness in the mind... when I don&#39;t meditate..</p>\n\n<hr />\n<p class=\"mentions-texteditor__content\">It seems ridiculous that a person who is convicted of an attempt to&nbsp;murder receives less punishment than a person who has committed a murder successfully. It&#39;s like we are rewarding the person for a failure. Furthermore, we are rewarding (reinforcing) development of his murder skills. It can also be seen as if the law is&nbsp;giving the person a second chance.&nbsp;</p>\n\n<hr />\n<p class=\"mentions-texteditor__content\">Stop the mind, watch the body. Stop the body, watch the mind. Two ways of meditation.&nbsp;</p>\n\n<p class=\"mentions-texteditor__content\">Human psyche is like water surface, small pebble/particles can create ripples, and then there are interference of these ripples which can create complicated state.&nbsp;</p>\n\n<p class=\"mentions-texteditor__content\">Is this glass half full, or half empty?</p>\n\n<p class=\"mentions-texteditor__content\">Let&#39;s see how we go about thinking on this:</p>\n\n<p class=\"mentions-texteditor__content\">We can see that glass is half full.</p>\n\n<p class=\"mentions-texteditor__content\">We can see that glass is half empty.</p>\n\n<p class=\"mentions-texteditor__content\">We can see that glass is both half full and half empty.</p>\n\n<p class=\"mentions-texteditor__content\">We can see that glass is neither half full or half empty.</p>\n\n<p class=\"mentions-texteditor__content\">We can question the definition of half, empty, and full.. What does even &quot;empty&quot; mean? Can a glass be half full without being half empty? What is reality, the emptiness or the fullness? - (Philosophers, mostly Western)</p>\n\n<p class=\"mentions-texteditor__content\">We can see that &quot;there is something that is holding some water. We can use that water in some ways. That&#39;s it.&quot; - &quot;Enlightened&quot; people.</p>\n\n<p class=\"mentions-texteditor__content\">We can see that glass, water, half and full are all illusions created by mind. - Easter Philosophers.&nbsp;</p>\n\n<hr />\n<p class=\"mentions-texteditor__content\">The power law is seen everywhere. So, in society you see that very few people have very high power over the rest of the society. If we decide to change it, how would we do that?</p>\n\n<p class=\"mentions-texteditor__content\">How about applying the structure of Swarm Intelligence to the principles of power?</p>\n\n<hr />\n<p class=\"mentions-texteditor__content\">Algebra, Geometry, Calculaus, Probability, Physics, Chemistry, Biology, ... blah&nbsp;blah&nbsp;blah... We teach all these things to people in schools and colleges without giving any meaning to this (if I&#39;m not mistaken), solving equations which don&#39;t mean anything, without a sense of wonder or appreciation (doesn&#39;t matter if pristigious institutes do it, if it is being taught anywhere it has to mean something, otherwise you are wasting precious life of people).&nbsp;</p>\n\n<p class=\"mentions-texteditor__content\">People after setting their foot on the jounrey of learning, there&nbsp;would 