ick to any particular idea or beleif? - It becomes very hard, it could be exausting before it, if ever, becomes liberating. So, how does one conduct a life while living in uncertainties? By developing a sense of discipline and responsibility. You shouldn&#39;t teach children that the world is made by God, or that we know that there&#39;s no God, no meaning, we are just a result of random mutations with no inherent purpose or meaning (even if it&#39;s true, let them find out by themselves). But teach them to conduct their life in a respectable manner, to respect themsleves, as well as others, induce the sense of oneness (since the theory of oneness is not going to be comphrehended by them).&nbsp;</p>\n\n<hr />\n<p class=\"mentions-texteditor__content\">For a person who thinks, if he has done something bad, the guilt itself becomes the most severe punishment, and if he has done something good, the satisfaction of having done itself becomes the best reward.&nbsp;</p>\n\n<hr />\n<p class=\"mentions-texteditor__content\">The strength of a collection, a society, a body etc is not exactly equal to the strength of its strongest part, but rather the strength of the weakest part. Society needs to meditate on this fact.</p>\n\n<hr />\n<p class=\"mentions-texteditor__content\">This drive for happiness - some people are even getting convinced by the neurological findings in the brains of meditators/monks that meditation is the way to go. The main point of these real monks is like dissolve the ego, the &quot;me&quot;. But if you try to do this you, even if you do something good, it might not actually make you happy, because you are still doing it for &quot;your&quot; happiness. On the other hand, if you don&#39;t try it won&#39;t come to you anyway.</p>\n\n<p class=\"mentions-texteditor__content\">So, how does one break this vicious circle?</p>\n\n<p class=\"mentions-texteditor__content\">I take a simple example of alarm clocks. When you set your alarm at some time in the morning. When the alarm goes off and you hear it, initially you will turn off the alarm and there&#39;s a high chance you will go back to sleep. If you continue doing this, there are two possibilities - at some point, you will start waking up at time, OR you will create a new habit where the alarm does not affect you. The same dynamics of the will works in the case above.</p>\n\n<hr />\n<p class=\"mentions-texteditor__content\">The world is just becoming complex, with the same fragments of pain, suffering, love, stealing, etc.. It just becomes more and more harder to distinguish evil from evil, good from non-good. All those things that ever existed, would always exist, the fabrics, the basics... It just becomes harder to spot them.</p>\n\n<hr />\n<p class=\"mentions-texteditor__content\">I&#39;m quite amazed by the workings of a simple insrtument like guitar. The creation of different sounds from slight variations in the way of handling the strings. The importance of silence and emergence of patterns.</p>\n\n<hr />\n<p class=\"mentions-texteditor__content\">What would all these enlightened people do when and if they live together without followers?</p>\n\n<p class=\"mentions-texteditor__content\">Probably they would act normal. Probably that&#39;s why they like to live in isolation or among followers/disciples.</p>\n\n<hr />\n<p class=\"mentions-texteditor__content\">Nothing will ever be enough, not even the <em>best</em>! Don&#39;t believe me? I&#39;ll give you a &quot;small&quot; proof: What happens when you see a <em>(new)</em> magic trick? See this in two phases: 1. Before intellectualizing on the tactics of the magic, 2. After intellectualizing the tactics of it. Do you feel a wonder? A beautiful experience?</p>\n\n<p class=\"mentions-texteditor__content\">If no, I wonder how you feel anything at all.... If you don&#39;t feel anything, you are good (best maybe, for yourself), and good for others as long as you are not psychopath.</p>\n\n<p class=\"mentions-texteditor_