;s world, the question arises:</p>\n\n<p>&nbsp;&nbsp; &quot;If a 3d simulation is a candidate for reality i.e. &#39;we are in a simulation&#39;, why can&#39;t the ideas themselves be real? Why can&#39;t the characters of a story be real? What&#39;s different in a 3d simulation than an ideological simulation?&quot;</p>\n\n<hr />\n<p>Everything happens for a reason, or reason is assigned after things happen for a length of time?</p>\n\n<p>E.g. They found Swearing comes from different part of the brain than where language comes from.. and it has many physiological and psychological effects. Did swearing occur because of the development of that part, or that part developed to facilitate swearing?</p>\n\n<hr />\n<p>Folk Philosophy:</p>\n\n<p>Me: Everything is impermanent, things, people etc..</p>\n\n<p>They: So what? Enjoy them as long as they are there!!</p>\n\n<p>Me: I don&#39;t know much, people know a lot...</p>\n\n<p>They: So what? There are people who appreciate me nevertheless. Enjoy that.</p>\n\n<p>Me: We don&#39;t know much about the universe etc..</p>\n\n<p>They: So what? How does it affect me?</p>\n\n<p>Me: We can remove suffering...</p>\n\n<p>They:&nbsp; But why do we have to remove it, suffering is what makes pleasure more enjoyable.</p>\n\n<p>Me:....</p>\n\n<hr />\n<p>Is becoming enlightened,&nbsp; equivalent to becoming a vegetable.</p>\n\n<blockquote>\n<p>&ldquo;Far better is it to dare mighty things, to win glorious</p>\n\n<p>triumphs, even though checkered by failure&hellip; than to</p>\n\n<p>rank with those poor spirits who neither enjoy nor</p>\n\n<p>suffer much, because they live in a gray twilight that</p>\n\n<p>knows not victory nor defeat.&rdquo;</p>\n\n<p>&mdash;Theodore Roosevelt</p>\n</blockquote>\n\n<hr />\n<blockquote>\n<p>&ldquo;Let the young know they will never find a more interesting, more</p>\n\n<p>instructive book than the patient himself.&rdquo;</p>\n\n<p>&mdash;Giorgio Baglivi</p>\n</blockquote>\n\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n\n<blockquote>\n<p>&l